stopbank
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:an embankment, used in low-lying rural areas to prevent large-scale flooding of pasture.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
